==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carmagnole
<hw>Car`ma`gnole"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A popular or Red Rebublican song and dance, of the time
of the first French Revolution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They danced and yelled the <qex>carmagnole</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Compton Reade.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bombastic report from the French armies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carman</ent>⟦br⟧
